      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Unaisis wrote:</div><div class="orig">i seen some awesome low man events with nin being the main attraction for tank and !!. I think its an awesome asset when wanting items without the hassle of forming big alliances and avoiding Elitist. </div></div>Everything is lowman now. Everything can be killed with whm+mnk, or rdm x2. You don't need any specific jobs for it. <br /> <br /> <br />My ls usually uses something along the lines of: <br /> <br />1-3 blm - TE/feet/KI farming <br />3-5 rdm/nin - nms, usually split into 2-3 groups of 1-3 people each. <br />rng - widescan, dd, !!, etc <br />blu - grellow, dd, etc <br />2 war, whm, brd, and maybe a sam - main party for harder nms, etc <br />nin - depends what we're doing, sometimes we bring a nin for red <br />mnk - for blue, depends how many we have, etc <br /> <br />The rest is typically either nothing, or mules sitting around by the blms leeching exp. Blms do all of the TE farming, and rdms do most of the nms. Works pretty great. If you don't have that many people, you can easily drop all dds except war, mnk, and nin (if you need to make sure you get red for atma, otherwise drop nin as well), and you've got a pretty good setup. <br /> <br />It's not the most efficient setup, but it gets the job done pretty damn well. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 21st 2010  3:34pm by ThePsychoticOne </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><s><a href="HTTP://ffxiah.com/player.php?id=1580273#item-sets" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiah.com/player.php?id=1580273#item-sets">Rog</a></s> <a href="HTTP://ffxirog.livejournal.com" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxirog.livejournal.com">lolLJ</a> <a href="HTTP://myanimelist.net/animelist/thepsychoticone" rel="external nofollow" title="myanimelist.net/animelist/thepsychoticone">Anime!</a> <br /><span class="sm"><s>75RDMBLMBRDNINRNG72(oc)DRK</s> <br />